benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: Valid Deletion: Successful cache invalidation for a valid account (204, empty body).
Non-Existent Resource: 404 for non-existent accounts and edge cases (no accounts, partially populated DB).
Missing accountId in path: 404 when accountId is not provided in the URL path.
Input Validation: 400 for invalid accountId formats (e.g., non-UUID patterns like abcd) and extreme lengths.
Authorization: 401 for unauthenticated access and for expired/invalid tokens.
Backend Unavailability: 503 responses when cache service is down or degraded (service unavailable).
Query Parameters: Endpoint accepts extra query parameters without affecting outcome (204).
HTTP Method Not Allowed: 405 for unsupported HTTP methods (e.g., GET on this endpoint).
Security: SQL injection attempts (e.g., accountId containing %27%20OR%20%271%27=%271) and XSS payloads yield 400.
Edge Cases: No accounts and partially populated databases result in 404 (account not found).
Performance: Concurrent DELETE requests across multiple accounts return 204 with average response time within 500ms.
Recovery: System recovers from transient network failures and subsequent retry succeeds.
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Re-using the same endpoint maintains 204 responses without regressions.
gaps: Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests validating how the API handles bursts of DELETE requests.
Caching Headers: No tests verifying caching semantics on DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control).
Internal Server Error Path (500): No test simulates 500 Internal Server Error conditions.
Forbidden Access (403): No tests for 403 responses beyond 401 (permissions issues).
Single-Resource Concurrency: No explicit test for race conditions deleting the same account concurrently.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling and resilience under burst loads.
Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on DELETE responses.
Add tests covering 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to ensure proper error handling.
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient-permission cases beyond 401.
Introduce explicit race-condition tests for concurrent deletes on the same account.
Expand boundary tests for accountId formats/lengths and verify idempotency on repeated DELETE requests.
